Fig. 4 . Binding of peptides to bimane-labeled HscA monitored by fluorescence quenching. Fractional quenching values determined from the integrated emission intensities in Fig. 3 were fit to hyperbolic saturation functions to determine K d and maximal quenching. HscA(D422C)-bimane: data for +Glu 98 –Cys 106 (▴) and +W-97 (○) were not fit, and the dashed curve shown was generated using K d = 30 μ m (max = 6%); +W-105 (□) K d = 9.8 μ m (max = 20.5%). HscA(A455C)-bimane: +Glu 98 –Cys 106 (▴) K d = 21.4 μ m (max = 29%), +W-97 (○) K d = 19.1 μ m (max = 68%), +W-105 (□, open squares ) K d = 19.2 μ m (max = 31%).

